Singapore hotel occupancy  RevPAR recover to pre-Covid-19 levels in Nov as international arrivals reach year-round high1. THE Singapore hotel sector has recorded its highest occupancy rates and revenue per available room (RevPAR) since the Covid-19 pandemic decimated the tourism industry.2. That's as the Republic welcomed 41 140 visitors in November  nearly double the 23 980 seen in the month before  the latest figures from the Singapore Tourism Board (STB) showed.3. November's tourist arrivals were up from 14 750 in the year-ago period  and also the highest seen in 2021 - despite remaining a far cry from the 240 000 travellers in March 2020  when Singapore took the unprecedented step of closing its borders to almost all short-term travel.More here
